'From Squeak 2.4b of April 23, 1999 on 29 June 1999 at 1:31:33 am'!"Change Set:		WnldStillCameraDate:			29 June 1999Author:			Jeff PierceImplements a still camera for Wonderlands (for use in the Actor Info tab)."!WonderlandCamera subclass: #WonderlandStillCamera	instanceVariableNames: ''	classVariableNames: ''	poolDictionaries: ''	category: 'Wonderland-Objects'!WonderlandCameraMorph subclass: #WonderlandStillCameraMorph	instanceVariableNames: ''	classVariableNames: ''	poolDictionaries: ''	category: 'Wonderland-Morphs'!!WonderlandStillCamera methodsFor: 'initialize-release' stamp: 'jsp 6/29/1999 01:01'!initializeFor: aWonderland	"Initializes the camera."	super initializeFor: aWonderland.		"Set the camera initial position"	composite translation: (B3DVector3 x: -1.5 y: 0.5 z: 2.6).	self turnTo: #(180 -30 180) duration: #rightNow.	"Initialize the camera viewing parameters"	perspective _ B3DCameraPerspective new.	self setFieldOfView: 40.0.	self setAspectRatio: 1.0.	self setNearClippingPlane: 0.1.	self setFarClippingPlane: 10000.0.	viewMatrix _ B3DMatrix4x4 new.	"Create a WonderlandCameraMorph for the camera to render into"	myMorph _ WonderlandStillCameraMorph new.	myMorph initializeWithCamera: self.	"Initially don't draw the scene background"	drawSceneBackground _ false.! !!WonderlandStillCameraMorph methodsFor: 'stepping' stamp: 'jsp 6/29/1999 01:07'!wantsSteps	^ false.! !!WonderlandStillCameraMorph methodsFor: 'controls' stamp: 'jsp 6/29/1999 01:20'!hideCameraControls	"Override our parent method to do nothing."! !!WonderlandStillCameraMorph methodsFor: 'controls' stamp: 'jsp 6/29/1999 01:20'!showCameraControls	"Override the parent method to do nothing."! !!WonderlandStillCameraMorph methodsFor: 'event handling' stamp: 'jsp 6/29/1999 01:08'!handlesMouseDown: evt	"We don't want to handle mouse up and down events, so return false"	^ false.! !!WonderlandStillCameraMorph methodsFor: 'event handling' stamp: 'jsp 6/29/1999 01:08'!handlesMouseOver: evt	"We don't want to handle mouse enter/leave events, so return false."	^ false.! !